# Cloudflare Pages redirects (https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/)
# Format:  /source  /destination  STATUS    (one rule per line, first match wins)
#
# Pages already handles these automatically, so they need NO rules here:
#   - pretty URLs:      /about     serves    /about.html
#   - trailing slashes: /about/    redirects to  /about
#
# Use 301 for anything that permanently moved or was retired (passes SEO link
# equity). 302 is temporary. 303 exists but is meant for post-form redirects,
# not content migration, so it is not used below.

# --- Old WordPress sitemap files (from the previous WP site) -> current sitemap ---
# Google discovered these from the old sitemap index; send them to the live one.
/sitemap-misc.xml       /sitemap.xml   301
/post-sitemap.xml       /sitemap.xml   301
/page-sitemap.xml       /sitemap.xml   301
/category-sitemap.xml   /sitemap.xml   301
/post_tag-sitemap.xml   /sitemap.xml   301
/archives-sitemap.xml   /sitemap.xml   301

# --- Retired / renamed pages: map old WordPress URLs to the new pages ---
# Fill these from Search Console > Indexing > Pages > "Not found (404)".
# One line per old URL. Examples (delete or edit to match your real old paths):
# /portfolio                 /work.html                          301
# /projects                  /work.html                          301
# /resume.pdf                /resume.html                        301
# /2024/06/pickleball-brand  /blog/pickleball-brand-from-zero.html   301
